snippet.textDisplay:
Now this is the problem i have with these arsenal fans. Yes you can only beat what's before you. But this is a very poor Newcastle team. And there were many times in that first half where Newcastle with better management of the football in that final third could have been 1 or two up in the first half. To hear these people talking about how good sako was, that really irks me. Sako and bellerien our two full back were insignificant in that first half. And but for a few runs in the second half, were not much better in the second half. The many occasions when the Newcastle wing man ran away from or pass bellerien on that left flank. Thanks to Pepe for turning up today, both in the attacking as well as the defensive end of the field
He along with Ozil would be my men of the match. Saved bellerien many times with his tracking back in the defense line.
Sako! Probably have some talent, but not at the point of keeping out kalasinac or Tierney out the team. The many times he turned over the play, after been fed good balls by auba and ozil, especially in that first half. Makes me have to ask the question, which match was these guys watching?
Another thing, most arsenal fans has been criticising Pepe and Ozil. With some, including yours truly, suggesting that they should be sold. Well let me say this; should Pepe or ozil leave arsenal and end up at a team with good midfielders, and forward who can link up and hold up the football, ala the arsenal of old. The arsenal fans now calling for them to go, will be begging for their return.
Just think about Gnabry now at Bayern Munich!
